50|$|<b>Radio</b> <b>watchkeeping</b> {{regulations}} advise all sea bound {{vessels to}} monitor channel 16 VHF when sailing, except when communicating on other marine channels for legitimate business or operational reasons. Coastguards {{and others are}} permitted to broadcast short informative safety messages on channel 16, however, it is an offence in most countries to make false mayday calls. When using the channel to call up ships or shore stations, the call has to be switched to a working channel after the initial response {{in order to keep}} channel 16 available to others.|$|E

